{"id":"rapha","term":"Rapha","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Tall. (1.) A Benjamite, the son of Binea (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 8:2\">1 Chr. 8:2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 8:37\">37</a>), a descendant of Saul. (2.) Margin of <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 20:4\">1 Chr. 20:4</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 20:6\">6</a>, where “giant” is given in the text.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 8:2","1 Chronicles 8:37","1 Chronicles 20:4","1 Chronicles 20:6"]}